				<category><![CDATA[AI]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[News]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[artificial intelligence]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[bubble]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[ChatGPT]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[NVIDIA]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[OpenAI]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[stock market]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://ventureburn.com/?p=203608</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>Tech markets are shifting rapidly today thanks to the rise of artificial intelligence. OpenAI, leading the charge, has seen its valuation rise from $20 billion in 2021 to over $850</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/ai-critic-ed-zitron-openai-might-collapse-stock-market/" data-wpel-link="internal">AI Tech Critic Ed Zitron Explains Why OpenAI Might Crash the Stock Market</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Tech markets are shifting rapidly today thanks to the rise of artificial intelligence. OpenAI, leading the charge, has seen its valuation rise from $20 billion in 2021 to over $850 billion as of July 2026. While this is one of the biggest growths we’ve ever seen, there are critics who believe OpenAI might crash soon. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Prominent tech critic Ed Zitron has issued a stark, terrifying warning that </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/openai-raises-110-billion-to-expand-global-ai-infrastructure/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">OpenAI</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> is heading straight toward a massive financial disaster. According to Zitron, the creator of ChatGPT represents the Lehman Brothers of AI.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Its eventual downfall will not happen in isolation. Instead, it could trigger a wider, catastrophic market meltdown. This crash could catch global investors completely off guard. The AI bubble is ready to pop, and the fallout will be massive.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">OpenAI’s Collapse Is a Matter of When, Not If</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Zitron </span><a href="https://www.wheresyoured.at/the-openai-bubble/#the-ai-bubble-is-an-openai-bubble-%E2%80%94-to-a-mortal-end" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">argues</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> that the current AI boom is built entirely on sand. It is simply not a sustainable business model. Because of this, he treats OpenAI’s ultimate downfall as an absolute certainty. In his view, the company has become load-bearing for the modern tech economy. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Tech giants are pouring hundreds of billions into data centers without seeing real returns. Zitron calls this trend the greatest capital misallocation in human history. The hype cannot sustain itself forever. Huge venture capital funding has kept the firm afloat for years. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">However, the clock is ticking louder each day. OpenAI recently filed confidential paperwork for an IPO. CEO Sam Altman is targeting a massive valuation up to $2 trillion. Critics believe this IPO is a desperate move to secure fresh cash before the music stops. The company cannot survive on empty promises anymore.</span></p>
<p><b><i>More Updates: </i></b><a href="https://ventureburn.com/swissto12-raises-70-million-series-c-multi-orbit-satellite/" data-wpel-link="internal"><b><i>SWISSto12 Raises $70M To Scale Multi-Orbit Business</i></b></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">The Numbers Backing the OpenAI Bubble</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The financial data reveals an alarming gap between marketing hype and fiscal reality. Zitron and the Financial Times recently reviewed OpenAI’s audited financial records from 2025. The actual results are shocking to read. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">OpenAI generated an impressive $13.07 billion in revenue. However, its total costs and operating expenses rocketed to $34 billion. This leaves a staggering $21 billion operating loss. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The total net loss looks even worse at $38.5 billion due to corporate structure reorganization. The cash burn rate is simply immense. For comparison, the company lost only $5 billion in 2024. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This steep trajectory shows that scaling up AI models only increases the financial bleeding. Furthermore, a $40 billion SoftBank loan comes due in early 2027. Time is running out to balance these massive books.</span></p>
<p><b><i>More Updates: </i></b><a href="https://ventureburn.com/brinc-raises-125-million-for-911-response-drones/" data-wpel-link="internal"><b><i>BRINC Raises $125M for 911 Response Drones in the U.S.</i></b></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">If OpenAI’s Bubble Bursts, the Rest of the Market Goes Down</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">A sudden collapse at OpenAI would send violent shockwaves through the global stock market. The main danger here is structural contagion. Major tech corporations have tied their balance sheets directly to OpenAI’s survival. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">For example, </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/2024/09/oracles-aws-partnership-reshapes-cloud-computings-future/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Oracle</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> carries $638 billion in performance obligations chained to AI infrastructure. Oracle’s stock has already dropped over 35% this year as investors wake up to this concentration risk. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Chip giant </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/nvidia-5-trillion-milestone/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">NVIDIA</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> also holds over $100 BILLION in related supply commitments. If OpenAI stops paying its bills, the entire domino chain falls down instantly. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Tech stocks would experience a punishing, historic correction. Zitron warns that this burst bubble will define the end of our current economic epoch. Investors need to watch these connected balance sheets very closely before it is too late.</span></p>
<p><b><i>More Updates: </i></b><a href="https://ventureburn.com/lumin-digital-raises-115m-to-drive-ai-banking/" data-wpel-link="internal"><b><i>Lumin Digital Raises $115M Valuation To Drive AI Banking</i></b></a></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/ai-critic-ed-zitron-openai-might-collapse-stock-market/" data-wpel-link="internal">AI Tech Critic Ed Zitron Explains Why OpenAI Might Crash the Stock Market</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
