					<description><![CDATA[<p>Fora reaches unicorn status with new funding round New York-based travel technology company Fora has raised $60 million in a Series D funding round, reaching a post-money valuation of $1</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/fora-raises-60m-series-d-ai-travel-advisors/" data-wpel-link="internal">Fora Raises $60M To Expand AI Platform For Travel Advisors</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>Fora reaches unicorn status with new funding round</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">New York-based travel technology company Fora has raised $60 million in a Series D funding round, reaching a post-money valuation of $1 billion as it accelerates the development of AI tools for travel advisors.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The round was led by Forerunner and Tactile Ventures. Thrive Capital, Insight Partners, Heartcore Capital, PLUS Capital, BlackPines Capital Partners, Tribeca Venture Partners, and even Amy Schumer, investing through the PLUS Capital collective. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">With this latest round, Fora’s total funding climbs to $138.5 million. The company’s got big plans for the money: making its AI platform even better, moving into new areas of travel, and pushing into markets overseas.</span></p>
<h2><b>AI aims to enhance rather than replace travel advisors<br />
</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_203606" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-203606" class="size-full wp-image-203606" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/a-vibrant-futuristic-poster-showcases-a-_k5Zr6IRhV9yfSPB6cPtyEQ_7m9BdPbQTN6MQgzNW0HgBg_cover.png" alt="A neon futuristic visual showing AI assisting travel advisors with planning and booking tasks." width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-203606" class="wp-caption-text">Fora combines AI automation with human expertise to streamline travel planning while preserving the personal touch. Source: Created by Ventureburn</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This platform takes care of all those tedious jobs—digging up destination info, sorting suppliers, building itineraries, and pulling together travel proposals. With less paperwork on their hands, advisors can focus on what really matters: sharing their own travel smarts and connecting with clients.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Evan Frank, the co-founder, isn’t worried about AI replacing people. In fact, he says it just makes great travel advisors even more valuable. Let the tech handle the busywork. People are still the ones who bring their own judgment, know-how, and a personal touch—the things you need for memorable trips.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Bottom line, the company uses AI as a support system for advisors. It streamlines the booking process but doesn’t get in the way of that human touch. That’s what sets high-end travel planning apart.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: <a href="https://ventureburn.com/whale-raises-40m-series-c-extension-enterprise-ai/" data-wpel-link="internal">Whale Raises $40M To Expand Enterprise AI Operating System Globally</a></span></p>
<h2><b>Rapid booking growth reflects rising demand</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company&#8217;s growth has accelerated significantly over the past year. It took three years to achieve its first $1 billion in lifetime bookings, followed by only eight months to reach $2 billion and another five months to surpass $3 billion.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Fora also points to broader momentum in the travel advisory profession. LinkedIn says travel advisor is now the fifth fastest-growing job in the U.S. for 2025. Right now, over 15,000 advisors are active on the platform. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Almost all of them, 97% started out in different fields like medicine, law, finance, or education. Some made the switch after retiring, and others just wanted a flexible way to earn some extra income.</span></p>
<h2><b>Expansion plans target new travel categories</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The new funding will help Fora expand beyond its current offerings by investing in categories including cruises, flights and enterprise </span><a href="https://navan.com/resources/glossary/travel-services" data-wpel-link="external" rel="external noopener noreferrer"><span style="font-weight: 400">travel services</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">. The company also plans to continue recruiting talent while enhancing Via&#8217;s AI capabilities across its advisor platform.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">“Fora combines the power of AI-driven automation with a personal touch to create a better travel experience than technology can alone,” said Brian O’Malley, managing partner and founder of tactile Ventures, a Fora investor. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">It’s a testament to how the use of AI in the workplace can enhance efficiency while keeping the human relationship intact. The future of AI and personal travel It’s on the minds of many as the rise of artificial intelligence makes inroads into professional services.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">To stay updated on crypto venture capital funding and market trends, visit our </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/category/news/venture-capital/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">venture capital news section</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> for more insights.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/fora-raises-60m-series-d-ai-travel-advisors/" data-wpel-link="internal">Fora Raises $60M To Expand AI Platform For Travel Advisors</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
