					<description><![CDATA[<p>Whale strengthens enterprise AI expansion with new funding Whale just raised another $40 million for its Series C round, bringing total Series C funding up to $100 million. That&#8217;s a</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/whale-raises-40m-series-c-extension-enterprise-ai/" data-wpel-link="internal">Whale Raises $40M To Expand Enterprise AI Operating System Globally</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>Whale strengthens enterprise AI expansion with new funding</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Whale just raised another $40 million for its Series C round, bringing total Series C funding up to $100 million. That&#8217;s a big boost, and it comes as more companies look for AI platforms that actually link their digital tools to real business operations.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">CMB International and SMBC Asia Rising Fund led this extension, while Krungsri Finnovate, Singtel Innov8, Hyundai Motor Group, and Charisma Partners joined in. The earlier round already featured backers like Bosch Ventures, MTR Lab, MDI Ventures, Gentree Fund, and Linear Capital.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">With this new funding, Whale’s planning to ramp up international growth, tighten relationships with enterprise customers, and build deeper links into local infrastructure. They&#8217;re eyeing bigger footprints in North America and Asia-Pacific next.</span></p>
<h2><b>AI platform connects physical operations with digital intelligence</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Founded by Jerry Ye, Whale has developed an AI Operating System designed to help organisations understand and automate physical business environments. Its proprietary Business World Model interprets information collected from cameras, sensors and audio devices.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This new funding shows that investors are putting their trust in AI tools that actually make a difference in how companies run, not just flashy standalone software. Whale’s planning to use the money to bring in new talent, boost its presence in different regions, and make its platform stronger—especially with more businesses looking for these kinds of solutions.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Right now, Whale already works with companies in retail, automotive, manufacturing, finance, food, healthcare, and telecom. The big goal? Help more organizations automate their workflows, tighten up compliance, and really understand what’s happening in their business.</span></p>
<h2><b>Investors back growing demand for enterprise AI operations<br />
</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_203602" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-203602" class="size-full wp-image-203602" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/a-futuristic-poster-depicting-a-swirling_piGLJGI1WGGfpRttmy_bDw_FKVGYztpToOBdZsLxNoK5A.png" alt="A neon futuristic visual showing AI transforming physical data into business intelligence across global industries." width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-203602" class="wp-caption-text">Whale’s AI platform enables enterprises to convert real-world data into actionable insights and scale operations globally. Source: Created by Ventureburn</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">CMB International highlighted Whale&#8217;s ability to execute complex enterprise AI deployments across multiple industries and markets. The investor believes the company&#8217;s technology foundation positions it for long-term global growth.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">SMBC Asia Rising Fund also pointed to Whale&#8217;s capability to organise data from physical environments into actionable business intelligence. The partnership is expected to combine Whale&#8217;s technology with SMBC Group&#8217;s international client network to accelerate adoption across industries.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Whale’s AI platform offers end-to-end capabilities to Krungsri Finnovate to support their operations in the ASEAN market, Hyundai Motor Group believes the technology can be utilized across sales, marketing, customer engagement and service areas of the Group’s businesses.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News:<a href="https://ventureburn.com/fireworks-ai-raises-1-5-billion-series-d/" data-wpel-link="internal"> Fireworks AI Raises $1.5 Billion to Expand Enterprise AI Infrastructure</a></span></p>
<h2><b>Funding supports broader international growth</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This new funding shows that investors are putting their trust in AI tools that actually make a difference in how companies run, not just flashy standalone software. Whale’s planning to use the money to bring in new talent, boost its presence in different regions, and make its platform stronger.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Right now, Whale already works with companies in retail, automotive, manufacturing, finance, food, healthcare, and telecom. The big goal? Help more organizations automate their workflows, tighten up </span><a href="https://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/compliance" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">compliance</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">, and really understand what’s happening in their business.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">As enterprises increasingly seek AI platforms that combine operational intelligence with automation, Whale believes its Business World Model provides a foundation for managing both digital and physical business environments at scale.</span></p>
