										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>Series D funding fuels enterprise AI growth</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Fireworks AI just landed $1.5 billion in Series D funding, shooting its valuation up to $17.5 billion. Demand’s booming for platforms that let companies build and launch their own AI models, and Fireworks is riding that wave.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">With this new investment, Fireworks plans to beef up its computing power, hire more engineers, and build tighter partnerships with leading cloud providers. The company also announced it’s now bringing in more than $1 billion in annualized revenue—a fivefold jump from last year.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Atreides Management, Index Ventures, and TCV led the round, with backing from heavyweights like NVIDIA, Lightspeed, Evantic Capital, Bessemer, Menlo Ventures, Insight Partners, Ontario Teachers’ Pension Plan, and Lone Pine Capital.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Founded in 2022 by Lin Qiao and six ex-Meta engineers, Fireworks helps organizations fine-tune open AI models. It aims to be a platform that organizations can use to build custom intelligence that suit their specific needs, rather than exclusively depend on </span><a href="https://iterate.ai/ai-glossary/closed-model-information" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">closed models</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">.</span></p>
<h2><b>Demand grows for specialised AI models<br />
</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_203598" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-203598" class="size-full wp-image-203598" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/a-futuristic-poster-showcases-a-vibrant-_5AnmdiErX82fOFTQ51k5GQ_OWS2nnV1QH275KtnPxaPDQ_cover.png" alt="A neon futuristic visual showing specialised AI models processing enterprise data across interconnected systems." width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-203598" class="wp-caption-text">Fireworks AI advances custom enterprise models as businesses shift toward specialised AI built on their own data. Source: Created by Ventureburn</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Fireworks AI expects the next generation of enterprise artificial intelligence to concentrate on models built for a specific company. Businesses each have a distinctive set of data, workstreams, and wisdom that may become specialized AI skill sets. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The organization has discovered approximately 95% of the tokens processed in its structure now come from custom models rather than the standard foundation models. Fireworks provides a portfolio of more than 200 text, graphics and multimodal models .</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/senra-systems-raises-65-million-wire-harness-manufacturing/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Senra Systems Raises $65 Million to Expand Aerospace Manufacturing Capacity</span></a></p>
<h2><b>Enterprise adoption accelerates platform growth</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Uber, Shopify, Doximity, Elastic, GitLab, and MongoDB all use the company’s services. Some fast-growing AI firms like Harvey and Cursor also rely on its infrastructure. And it’s not just the clients—the numbers tell a story too. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Earlier this year, Fireworks pushed even further by teaming up with Microsoft. Now, Microsoft customers get access to AI models on the Fireworks platform, powered by computing resources from more than 20 different infrastructure providers.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Gavin Baker, who runs Atreides Management, sees a trend here. He thinks more businesses will start mixing advanced AI models with customized open-source options that fit their own needs. Daily token volume running through their platform jumped from 15 trillion to over 40 trillion.</span></p>
<h2><b>Investment supports infrastructure expansion</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company plans to invest the fresh funds in growing its global compute infrastructure, adding more engineers and beefing up ties with cloud providers. Fireworks has 200 employees at present, and is expected to grow this by three-times by the year’s end amid sustained demand.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company’s specialist models are on par or better for several business specific uses at much lower cost than closed models, it says. Fireworks is betting on enterprises increasingly looking for increased control over AI performance, costs, and data security.</span></p>
